twitch-tag-media (1.0.0) stable; urgency=low

  * Extract artist-name transforms into Daybo::Twitch::Transforms; make
    fixConjunctions and fixWorldSuffix private with unit tests (#70, #97).
  * Add streamlink-recorder filename format support (#93).
  * Add Log4perl logging: replace --verbose/-v with --log-level/-L
    accepting Log4perl level names; add --stats flag; add --json for
    structured JSON log output; add coloured level output (#69).
  * Add AAC and AC3 backends (delegate to MP4 backend).
  * Add M4A backend (delegates to MP4 backend).
  * Add Opus backend via opustags.
  * Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM gracefully, forwarding signals to children (#85).
  * Introduce BaseObject with singleton Logger via MooseX::Singleton and
    MooseX::ClassAttribute; route all logging through Logger::emit.
  * Add comprehensive unit test suite covering all backends and core methods
    (#48).
  * Add CI pipeline configurations for GitHub Actions, BitBucket Pipelines,
    and SourceHut builds.sr.ht (#77).
  * Fix: count tag changes when file has no prior tags.
  * Fix: opustags read — drop unsupported -l flag (v1.10.1 compatibility).
  * Fix: rename Opus.pm → OPUS.pm to match package name convention.

 -- Rev. Duncan Ross Palmer <2e0eol@gmail.com>  Sat, 31 May 2026 15:34:00 +0100

twitch-tag-media (0.10.0) stable; urgency=low

  * Add MKV support via mkvpropedit: read/write tags to Matroska files
    (#73).
  * Add --delay/-d flag to throttle file dispatch rate; supports
    sub-millisecond precision.
  * Add --atime, --ctime, --mtime flags to skip recently-modified files.
  * Switch percentage display to two decimal places (#76).
  * Add elapsed time and ETA to per-file progress messages.
  * Replace --directory/-d with positional PATH arguments; supports
    multiple directories.
  * Add dynamic concurrency mode: --jobs=0 auto-adjusts to CPU count per
    iteration (#66).
  * Rename 'Tag changes' stat to 'Tags altered' to clarify it counts tag
    fields, not files.
  * Fix --json to imply --verbose (#54).
  * Fix: skip .temp.<ext> files still being downloaded by yt-dlp (#75).
  * Fix: treat unrecognised filename patterns as unqualified (#64).
  * Add mkvtoolnix, ffmpeg, libuniversal-require-perl, and
    libreadonly-perl to Debian runtime dependencies.

 -- Rev. Duncan Ross Palmer <2e0eol@gmail.com>  Tue, 14 Apr 2026 21:30:00 +0100

